  "name": "RC Cells",
  "type": "feat",
  "_id": "02crmhRO6e7LQhq3",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Ghoul.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong data-start=\"97\" data-end=\"123\">Beginning at 1st level</strong>, you have a pool of special cells known as <strong data-start=\"167\" data-end=\"179\">RC Cells</strong>. These cells are naturally produced by Ghouls in abundance and are used to fuel your abilities. You have a number of RC Cells equal to your level + your Constitution modifier per long rest.</p><p data-start=\"373\" data-end=\"433\">Once per turn, you can use RC Cells in the following ways:</p><ul data-start=\"435\" data-end=\"1271\"><li data-start=\"435\" data-end=\"697\"><strong data-start=\"437\" data-end=\"463\">Ghoulish Regeneration:</strong> As a Bonus Action, you may spend any number of RC Cells, kicking your body's natural regeneration into overdrive. For the next minute, at the start of each of your turns, you regain hit points equal to the number of RC Cells spent.</li><li data-start=\"698\" data-end=\"879\"><strong data-start=\"700\" data-end=\"722\">Ghoulish Strength:</strong> When you deal damage with a melee attack, you can spend any number of remaining RC Cells, dealing additional damage equal to three times the amount spent.</li><li data-start=\"880\" data-end=\"1109\"><strong data-start=\"882\" data-end=\"903\">Ghoulish Agility:</strong> Whenever you make a Dexterity saving throw or an Athletics/Acrobatics check, you may spend any number of RC Cells, adding a <strong data-start=\"1028\" data-end=\"1035\">1d6</strong> bonus for the first RC Cell and a <strong data-start=\"1070\" data-end=\"1076\">+1</strong> bonus for each past the first.</li><li data-start=\"1110\" data-end=\"1271\"><strong data-start=\"1112\" data-end=\"1130\">Kagune Repair:</strong> Starting at 3rd level, when your Kagune is broken, you can choose to spend <strong data-start=\"1206\" data-end=\"1220\">3 RC Cells</strong> to repair it, allowing it to be activated again.</li></ul>",
